\subsection*{Mindmap}

Regarding available data determining RNA localization can be suggested as follows:

\tikzstyle{startstop} = [rectangle, rounded corners, minimum width=1cm, minimum height=1cm,text centered, text=black1, draw=yellow1, fill=yellow1]
\tikzstyle{io} = [trapezium, trapezium left angle=70, trapezium right angle=110, minimum width=3cm, minimum height=1cm, text centered, text=black1, draw=blue1, fill=blue1]
\tikzstyle{process} = [rectangle, minimum width=1cm, minimum height=1cm, text centered, text=black1, draw=red1, fill=red1, align=center]
\tikzstyle{decision} = [diamond, minimum width=1cm, minimum height =1cm, text centered, text=black1, draw=green1, fill=green1]

\tikzstyle{arrow} = [thick,->,>=stealth, color=black1]

\begin{tikzpicture}[node distance=2cm]

  \node (start) [startstop] {start};
  \node (in1) [io, below of=start] {RNA Sequence, Gene Name, Gene Sequence};
  \node (rnalocate) [process, below of=in1] {Fitting with RNALocate};
  \node (tcga) [process, below of=rnalocate] {Looking up trough TCGA};
  \node (path) [process, right = of tcga] {Looking up trough \\ KEGG, \\ Cyclebase, \\ other cancer related DBs};
  \node (expressionpattern) [process, left = of tcga] {Looking up trough BioGPS and Bgee};
  \node (dec1) [decision, below = of tcga] {Decision: Localization probability};
  \node (end) [startstop, below = of dec1] {end};

  \draw [arrow] (start) -- (in1);
  \draw [arrow] (in1) -- (rnalocate);

  \draw [arrow] (rnalocate) -- (tcga);
  \draw [arrow] (rnalocate) -- (expressionpattern);
  \draw [arrow] (rnalocate) -- (path);

  \draw [arrow] (tcga) -- (rnalocate);
  \draw [arrow] (tcga) -- (dec1);

  \draw [arrow] (path) |- (rnalocate);
  \draw [arrow] (path) -- (dec1);

  \draw [arrow] (expressionpattern) |- (rnalocate);
  \draw [arrow] (expressionpattern) -- (dec1);

  \draw [arrow] (dec1) -- (end);

\end{tikzpicture}

